oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Judge Hamby Reunion
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Judge Hamby's reunion on Main Street in Crossville. Street scene which shows First National Bank on the left. Also shows a marching band in the street.

Judge Hamby may refer to William A. Hamby, who was a county judge for Cumberland County for 26 years. In 1889-1908, Judge William A. Hamby was one of the earliest officials holding office in Cumberland County even though he had served in the Confederate army. He died June 5, 1919, and is buried in the Crossville City Cemetery.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
